WEBVTT

00:02.586 --> 00:05.749
COLIN: Now, be yourselves
and just speak from the heart.

00:05.923 --> 00:06.912
Jimmy, Chloe...

00:07.091 --> 00:10.254
...I can 't tell you how happy I am
the two of you found each other.

00:10.427 --> 00:12.839
You're very lucky to be together.

00:13.222 --> 00:16.134
Your wedding day is gonna be perfect.
I'm gonna make sure of it.

00:16.308 --> 00:18.890
Stop hogging the spotlight, Smallville.

00:19.061 --> 00:21.052
Hey, coz, you know that I love you...

00:21.230 --> 00:26.145
...and I wish you and Jimmy
long and happy years together.

00:26.318 --> 00:28.434
And remember what the general
always says:

00:28.612 --> 00:32.730
"Marriage is the only war
where you get to sleep with the enemy. "

00:34.326 --> 00:37.443
-You can edit out that last part, right?
-Lois.

00:37.621 --> 00:39.407
I told him.

00:41.083 --> 00:43.074
[GUESTS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

00:45.921 --> 00:47.912
[PACHELBEL'S "CANON" PLAYING]

00:57.266 --> 00:59.257
[GUESTS APPLAUDING]

01:22.166 --> 01:25.283
MINISTER:
I now pronounce you husband and wife.

01:25.461 --> 01:27.827
You may kiss the bride.

01:28.881 --> 01:30.121
[CH UCKLES]

01:30.924 --> 01:32.915
[GUESTS APPLAUDING]

01:33.635 --> 01:35.296
[GUESTS CHEER]

01:38.932 --> 01:40.593
[CH UCKLES]

01:41.477 --> 01:44.685
Ladies and gentlemen,
join me in welcoming the newlyweds.

02:03.791 --> 02:04.826
MAN:
Do it. Yeah, do it.

02:05.000 --> 02:06.331
[THUD FROM ABOVE]

02:07.085 --> 02:08.950
Who was that?

02:09.129 --> 02:11.415
[GROWLING NEARBY]

02:13.550 --> 02:14.801
COLIN:
Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

02:14.968 --> 02:16.003
[GROWLING NEARBY]

02:16.178 --> 02:17.714
MAN 1:
Go. Get outside. Go. Go, go!

02:17.888 --> 02:20.971
COLIN: Somebody help!
MAN 2: Come on, get out. Please.

02:22.059 --> 02:23.219
MAN 1:
No! Aah!

02:23.811 --> 02:25.676
Hold on, Jimmy.

02:26.271 --> 02:27.727
Please, don't leave me.

02:27.898 --> 02:29.229
[CRASH NEARBY]

02:29.399 --> 02:31.890
MAN 2: There's another door at the back.
Go that way.

02:32.069 --> 02:33.354
Get down! Get down!

02:33.529 --> 02:35.440
WOMAN:
This way.

02:35.697 --> 02:37.233
[CHLOE SCREAMS]

03:35.215 --> 03:37.456
MAN 1: Here you go.
MAN 2: Thanks a lot. I got it.

03:38.844 --> 03:40.459
It's 1100 hours, people.

03:40.637 --> 03:43.424
We only got till sunset
to change this little heifer house...

03:43.599 --> 03:46.966
...into my cousin's chapel of love,
so let's pick up the pace.

03:47.144 --> 03:48.475
Whoa, hold on, Emeril.

03:48.645 --> 03:51.637
Dinnenivare stays outside
until the reception. Presto, change-o.

03:51.815 --> 03:53.055
Of course, no problem.

03:53.233 --> 03:56.942
Goldilocks, this is Mother Goose,
what's the status at Bridal Central?

03:57.362 --> 03:59.023
Ahead of schedule. Good job, Chloe.

03:59.197 --> 04:02.439
But don't get cocky or you'll fall behind.
Over and out.

04:02.701 --> 04:06.068
Oh. Uh, Jimmy told me you're going to be
ﬁlming this epic, Spielberg.

04:06.246 --> 04:09.989
I want testimonials, candids, everything,
but I don't wanna know you're here.

04:10.167 --> 04:12.658
-You're a ﬂy on the wall, all right?
-Ring that bell.

04:13.337 --> 04:14.543
No.

04:18.133 --> 04:20.169
Mother Goose to Baby Bear.

04:20.385 --> 04:23.092
Mother Goose to Baby Bear.
Come in, Baby Bear.

04:23.263 --> 04:24.673
I'm getting married.

04:24.848 --> 04:27.430
Shouldn't I get bumped up to Papa Bear?

04:28.310 --> 04:29.675
Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa.

04:29.853 --> 04:32.310
We don't need to jinx her big day.

04:32.522 --> 04:34.262
Seem a little twitchy there, Jimmy.

04:34.441 --> 04:36.682
Butterﬂies in your stomach
starting to do the rumba yet?

04:36.860 --> 04:38.600
Well, the only thing I'm nervous about...

04:38.779 --> 04:41.521
...is seeing Chloe before the ceremony.
It's bad luck.

04:42.240 --> 04:45.528
What about the whole
till-death-do-us-part part?

04:45.702 --> 04:47.693
That's gotta be nerve-racking.

04:48.080 --> 04:50.492
Well, when you pick the right person...

04:50.999 --> 04:52.990
...there's no need for wedding-day jitters.

04:56.088 --> 04:57.669
Good answer, Jimbo.

04:57.839 --> 05:00.706
Speaking of, since you don't have
a plus one tonight...

05:00.884 --> 05:02.875
...I'd like you to meet one of my friends.

05:03.053 --> 05:05.089
Name's Clark Kent.

05:05.263 --> 05:08.346
-You heard of him?
-Put away your bow and arrow, Cupid.

05:08.517 --> 05:11.509
That bumbling tadpole
is not my prince charming.

05:11.687 --> 05:15.305
Well, maybe you just need to jump
his lily pad and plant one on him.

05:15.482 --> 05:19.225
Come on, I've seen the way
you two look at each other.

05:20.404 --> 05:21.393
[SCOFFS]

05:21.571 --> 05:23.732
You need to get your eyesight checked,
Olsen.

05:24.074 --> 05:28.067
Clark doesn't like me,
he likes driving me crazy.

05:28.245 --> 05:29.735
Flirtation 101, Lane.

05:29.913 --> 05:32.996
I mean, that's what a guy does
when he's into a girl.

05:35.502 --> 05:37.038
Really?

05:37.212 --> 05:38.748
Trust me...

05:38.922 --> 05:41.584
...Lois and Clark would be great together.

05:42.384 --> 05:43.840
Feel it in my gut.

05:44.011 --> 05:45.342
[CH UCKLES]

05:46.054 --> 05:48.045
Well, take some ex-lax and get over it.

05:48.223 --> 05:49.258
[CH UCKLES]

05:49.433 --> 05:53.096
Okay, well, I'm gonna go practice my vows.
When you see Mr. Right, give him this.

05:53.770 --> 05:55.931
-Okay.
-Thank you.

06:05.782 --> 06:06.942
[LENS WHIRRING]

06:08.702 --> 06:12.035
If you don't get that camera out of my face,
I'm gonna ring your bell.

06:12.205 --> 06:15.538
I guess the groom's more frazzled
than he thought. I forgot my bow tie.

06:17.794 --> 06:19.125
Wow!

06:20.297 --> 06:21.878
You look great.

06:22.049 --> 06:23.630
Hey, cowboy.

06:23.800 --> 06:25.131
Wanna give a girl a hand?

06:26.595 --> 06:29.928
Oh, my God. I'm not supposed to see you
till the wedding.

06:30.098 --> 06:31.599
Okay, you know what, cut. Cut.

06:31.767 --> 06:33.303
COLIN:
Oh, come on, Jimmy.

06:33.477 --> 06:35.138
This is classic.

06:35.312 --> 06:36.973
Just go, go.

06:37.355 --> 06:39.641
I, uh.... I called your phone
and you didn't answer.

06:39.816 --> 06:42.273
I thought that you were getting
your hair coiffed.

06:42.444 --> 06:44.309
I made the appointment earlier.

06:44.821 --> 06:47.312
| wish you would've told me.
I wouldn't have come over.

06:47.824 --> 06:49.985
Jimmy, it's ﬁne. Calm down.

06:51.286 --> 06:53.493
No, you don't get it. This is a--

06:53.663 --> 06:54.743
It's a disaster.

06:54.915 --> 06:56.075
Maybe it's not so bad.

06:56.249 --> 06:58.581
I mean, my garter belt
is a little bit temperamental.

06:58.752 --> 07:00.288
Maybe it's good luck that you came by.

07:00.462 --> 07:04.000
Groom sees the bride before the wedding?
It's like the Hindenburg of disasters.

07:04.174 --> 07:07.792
-Worse than black cats, broken mirrors and—
-Jimmy, breathe.

07:07.969 --> 07:10.506
Look, our love
has weathered federal arrests...

07:10.680 --> 07:13.968
...and heart-attack-inducing kisses
and a freakazoid bout of amnesia.

07:14.142 --> 07:17.475
I think that we'll survive this.

07:18.522 --> 07:19.853
[CHLOE EXHALES]

07:23.193 --> 07:24.524
[CHLOE CHUCKLES]

07:25.862 --> 07:27.363
That's better.

07:35.497 --> 07:38.580
No, I guess me showing up
is just a sign...

07:38.750 --> 07:41.241
...that when no one else
is around to help...

07:42.129 --> 07:44.085
...we'll always be there for each other.

07:44.256 --> 07:45.792
Forever.

07:48.468 --> 07:50.208
Perfect.

07:54.558 --> 07:57.220
-l'm gonna go get my bow tie.
-Okay.

08:01.565 --> 08:02.896
[CHLOE CHUCKLES]

08:05.068 --> 08:06.683
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

08:15.078 --> 08:16.659
DAVIS [OVER PHONE]:
Chloe, it's Davis.

08:16.830 --> 08:20.414
Look, I know I'm the last person
you wanna talk to today...

08:20.584 --> 08:22.415
...but, ahh, please, call me back.

08:22.586 --> 08:24.417
VOICEMAIL:
To delete this message press-

08:24.588 --> 08:26.078
JIMMY:
Who was that?

08:26.715 --> 08:28.376
Brigadier General Lois...

08:28.550 --> 08:32.793
...Ietting us know that, uh, we have
T-minus three hours until D-day.

08:33.430 --> 08:37.924
So, what do you say we get ready
to storm the beach, handsome?

08:38.685 --> 08:40.346
[JIMMY CHUCKLES]

08:53.783 --> 08:56.399
[CATERERS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

08:56.578 --> 08:58.785
CATERER:
Are we keeping these cold?

08:59.164 --> 09:00.324
This is cold.

09:03.126 --> 09:04.787
CLARK:
Oliver.

09:04.961 --> 09:07.043
Watch out for Lois.
She'll pin an apron on you...

09:07.214 --> 09:09.455
...and name you after
some sort of fairy-tale character.

09:09.633 --> 09:11.294
What's wrong?

09:12.177 --> 09:13.883
Lex is alive.

09:15.472 --> 09:19.636
I was tracking a wireless ghost router
he used to bounce e-mails to Tess Mercer.

09:19.809 --> 09:23.643
If we can get our hands on that router,
it'll tell us where the e-mails originated.

09:24.814 --> 09:26.224
It's not like Lex to leave a trail.

09:26.399 --> 09:29.857
He's not leaving a trail.
His routers pop up all over the globe.

09:30.028 --> 09:32.770
But every time I show up,
all the hardware's missing.

09:34.491 --> 09:37.574
You want me to grab the router
the next time Lex sends an e-mail.

09:37.744 --> 09:39.029
That's right.

09:39.204 --> 09:41.741
Based on the previous pattern,
I'm expecting one today.

09:41.915 --> 09:44.327
We could be hours away
from locking that monster up.

09:44.501 --> 09:46.708
I can't do this today.

09:46.878 --> 09:49.494
What? You've given Lex, like,
a hundred second chances.

09:49.673 --> 09:52.710
And if he's out there alive,
he hasn't made a move for months.

09:52.884 --> 09:55.626
This can wait 24 hours. Chloe can't.

09:55.804 --> 09:57.544
The wedding?

09:58.348 --> 10:01.181
Is that the real reason you don't wanna go
or is that just an excuse?

10:01.351 --> 10:02.591
Chloe's gonna understand.

10:02.769 --> 10:04.305
No, she won't.

10:05.355 --> 10:07.186
When I had Jor-El
bring back her memories...

10:07.357 --> 10:10.190
...I asked him to leave out the ones
about who I really am.

10:10.360 --> 10:12.476
You know everything she's suffered
because of me.

10:12.654 --> 10:14.861
And not to give her away
on her wedding day...

10:15.031 --> 10:16.646
...it's not an option.

10:17.867 --> 10:20.074
Maybe Lex hasn't made his move yet...

10:20.245 --> 10:22.031
...but he will.

10:23.164 --> 10:25.951
He's more dangerous now
than he ever was.

10:26.710 --> 10:29.497
Chloe may not know
your secret anymore...

10:29.879 --> 10:31.665
...but Lex still does.

10:48.356 --> 10:50.347
[CLARK APPROACHES]

10:51.901 --> 10:53.186
Oliver.

10:54.446 --> 10:56.858
Sorry it took so long.
The warehouse was guarded.

10:57.032 --> 10:59.148
It's a good thing
the infamous red-blue blur...

10:59.326 --> 11:01.612
...is faster than a speeding bullet.

11:02.370 --> 11:03.746
So let's see it.

11:05.707 --> 11:07.743
Is that what this is about?

11:09.753 --> 11:13.371
Oliver, you told me
you set aside your need for vengeance.

11:14.716 --> 11:17.378
I know you hate Lionel
for what he did to your parents.

11:17.552 --> 11:19.713
Did? Clark, it's called murder.

11:19.888 --> 11:22.004
You can't punish the son
for sins of the father.

11:22.182 --> 11:23.888
That's not what I'm doing.

11:25.310 --> 11:26.925
Oliver.

11:27.812 --> 11:29.427
I remember when my dad died.

11:29.606 --> 11:33.770
I was so angry, I almost crossed a line
that I could not come back from.

11:33.943 --> 11:36.776
I'm not gonna let you make
the same mistake.

11:39.115 --> 11:41.276
The truth is I'm going after Lex for you.

11:42.369 --> 11:43.734
That's only half the truth.

11:43.912 --> 11:47.621
Clark. You know how dangerous this guy is.
He may even know how to kill you.

11:50.627 --> 11:53.084
Why don't you
just give me the router, okay?

11:53.254 --> 11:56.166
It's gonna take me a couple of hours
to download it anyway.

11:56.466 --> 11:58.923
Plenty of time to eat cake
and do the chicken dance...

11:59.094 --> 12:01.085
...before you even take off.

12:01.971 --> 12:04.804
No. I'm gonna keep this
until after the wedding.

12:07.227 --> 12:09.764
If you're really doing this for me, Oliver...

12:10.939 --> 12:13.146
...you'll wait until I can go with you.

12:26.955 --> 12:28.161
What's with the ﬁreworks?

12:29.999 --> 12:32.251
He took the router with him.

12:32.419 --> 12:34.410
Without that thing,
I can't make my move.

12:35.004 --> 12:37.256
Put out the fuse, dude.

12:37.424 --> 12:38.459
Wi-Fi.

12:38.633 --> 12:42.717
I downloaded the info while you two
were having that lovers' spat.

13:06.119 --> 13:08.030
My God.

13:08.746 --> 13:12.989
I have too much to do to start crying,
but you look breathtaking.

13:13.877 --> 13:17.711
If it wasn't for you, I would look more like
the bride of Frankenstein than Cinderella.

13:17.881 --> 13:21.999
What you did to this barn
is absolutely amazing, Lois.

13:22.510 --> 13:23.841
[CH UCKLES]

13:24.721 --> 13:26.382
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

13:27.557 --> 13:29.343
Gonna answer that?

13:37.108 --> 13:39.724
-What's wrong?
-Nothing.

13:42.572 --> 13:45.939
It's Davis Bloome.
He's been calling all day.

13:46.117 --> 13:47.857
Deep down, I know he's a great guy.

13:48.036 --> 13:49.901
I just think he's a little confused.

13:53.374 --> 13:54.955
Last week, he kissed me.

13:55.126 --> 13:57.742
And he told me he wasn't gonna let me
marry the wrong guy.

13:59.422 --> 14:03.165
Are you starting to have feelings
for tall, dark and scary?

14:04.135 --> 14:08.424
All I want is to walk down that aisle
and marry the man I love.

14:10.808 --> 14:14.221
Uh, when did you know he was the one?

14:17.607 --> 14:19.814
Lois, don't worry.

14:19.984 --> 14:22.691
When you meet your super stud,
you'll know.

14:25.114 --> 14:28.902
Please, this isn't about me.
I need to get bitten by the love bug...

14:29.077 --> 14:31.409
...about as much as I need a bite
from a black widow.

14:31.579 --> 14:32.989
CHLOE:
Mm.

14:33.831 --> 14:35.742
-Do you have everything you need?
-Almost.

14:35.917 --> 14:38.499
I have something old, something blue,
something new...

14:38.670 --> 14:42.333
...and Ijust need something borrowed
to round out the tradition.

14:42.507 --> 14:43.838
LOIS:
Huh.

14:44.300 --> 14:45.460
Aha.

14:46.427 --> 14:50.966
When in trouble, leave it to Clark Kent
to get you out of a jam.

14:51.140 --> 14:53.472
Let's see what we have here.

14:58.356 --> 14:59.687
Huh.

15:02.068 --> 15:03.569
What are you two girls doing?

15:03.736 --> 15:05.988
The bride needs something borrowed
to take to the altar.

15:06.155 --> 15:09.147
How about she carry your piece
of Smallville's ﬁnest meteor rock...

15:09.325 --> 15:10.485
...down the aisle?

15:11.202 --> 15:13.488
Hey, why don't you put that away? I--

15:13.663 --> 15:15.324
I have a better idea.

15:30.305 --> 15:33.342
You gave that to me freshman year
at the homecoming dance.

15:36.477 --> 15:38.854
And you kept it all this time?

15:39.022 --> 15:41.513
I never throw away good memories.

15:46.321 --> 15:47.811
Thanks, Smallville.

15:48.698 --> 15:51.360
Another pre-wedding ﬁre put out.

15:54.829 --> 15:56.865
If you're all set,
you and I have to vamoose.

15:57.040 --> 16:00.373
It's almost high noon
and we have a showdown to get ready for.

16:50.426 --> 16:51.677
Goodbye, Lex.

17:25.628 --> 17:27.619
[GREEN ARROW GRUNTING]

17:32.510 --> 17:34.626
WOMAN:
Oliver Queen?

17:38.808 --> 17:40.469
Lana?

17:43.646 --> 17:47.230
So Oliver Queen moonlights
as Green Arrow.

17:47.400 --> 17:49.482
Does Clark know about you?

17:49.652 --> 17:53.236
I think I can safely say he knows
more of my secrets than he does yours.

17:53.406 --> 17:56.239
You're not gonna tell me
you're down here on vacation, are you?

17:56.409 --> 17:57.990
We both know that two hours ago...

17:58.161 --> 18:01.153
...more than 430,000 megagigs
of LuthorCorp RAM...

18:01.330 --> 18:03.946
...and Ethernet cables
were running through this place.

18:04.125 --> 18:06.832
Sounds like we each came here
with a score to settle.

18:10.006 --> 18:13.214
I'd say you were aiming to settle
more than a score.

18:17.388 --> 18:19.299
He leave this note for you or me?

18:20.433 --> 18:22.890
I'm not convinced Lexis alive.

18:23.060 --> 18:27.474
Just because the king dies, doesn't mean
the entire empire crumbles overnight.

18:28.316 --> 18:31.649
I just followed the leads here
to protect Clark.

18:31.819 --> 18:33.195
Good.

18:33.529 --> 18:36.862
Because no one else seems too concerned
that Lex found out his secret.

18:38.701 --> 18:41.818
If you're on a trail, I can help you.

18:42.872 --> 18:44.533
Is this your version of help?

18:44.707 --> 18:47.073
Because it seems a little personal to me.

18:47.251 --> 18:49.503
You're Green Arrow,
you're better than this.

18:52.215 --> 18:54.331
You sound like Clark.

18:58.554 --> 19:01.045
If we wanna ﬁght for the greater good...

19:01.224 --> 19:03.715
...maybe we all have to be
a little more like Clark.

19:13.945 --> 19:15.606
Oliver.

19:17.824 --> 19:19.564
How is he?

19:24.288 --> 19:26.904
You know, he's giving Chloe away
at her wedding.

19:28.042 --> 19:29.907
You can come ﬁnd out.

19:32.046 --> 19:33.707
No, I can't.

19:33.881 --> 19:35.746
It's too complicated.

19:37.885 --> 19:41.218
She's your best friend
and it's her wedding day.

19:41.389 --> 19:43.880
I don't understand
what's so complicated about that.

19:46.936 --> 19:50.428
You just said we need to be
more like Clark, right?

19:53.150 --> 19:54.890
Well, what would he do?

20:01.868 --> 20:03.324
LOIS:
Smallville. chop-chop, let's go.

20:03.494 --> 20:06.577
We can't have a wedding
without the escort to give the bride away.

20:19.135 --> 20:20.466
[SIGHS]

20:21.262 --> 20:23.127
Looks like you're ready.

20:24.181 --> 20:27.014
I have it all under control.
Except for these cuff links.

20:27.184 --> 20:30.676
They were my dad's
and I've never had to put them on before.

20:31.105 --> 20:33.471
I guess you don't have much need
for cuff links...

20:33.649 --> 20:37.562
...when you have a whole closet
full of ﬂannel shirts, huh, Farmer John?

20:37.987 --> 20:40.319
Big city boy, let me give you a lesson.

20:41.616 --> 20:46.485
You just have to make sure this part
sticks up straight and then it slides right in.

20:52.960 --> 20:56.828
Heh. The ring, you can give that to Jimmy
when the minister signals.

20:57.006 --> 20:59.418
And here are his vows in case he forgets.

21:04.055 --> 21:05.386
[SIGHS]

21:06.349 --> 21:08.465
"It's really hard for me to—

21:09.143 --> 21:11.475
To put my feelings into words.

21:11.646 --> 21:13.932
But from the moment we met...

21:14.106 --> 21:17.143
...I knew I wanted to spend
the rest of my life with you."

21:21.614 --> 21:23.479
Jimmy's vows--

21:24.408 --> 21:26.273
They're really sweet.

21:31.707 --> 21:34.289
Yeah, he's a regular Cyrano.

21:37.630 --> 21:41.543
COLIN: Hey, guys, how about a testimonial
before the ceremony?

21:42.385 --> 21:43.465
-Sure.
-Great.

21:43.636 --> 21:47.049
All right. Now, be yourselves
and just speak from the heart.

21:47.223 --> 21:49.714
Jimmy, Chloe, I can't tell you
how happy I am...

21:49.892 --> 21:51.507
...the two of you found each other.

21:51.686 --> 21:53.222
You're very lucky to be together.

21:55.272 --> 21:57.729
Chloe, I know you're not picking up
because of what happened.

21:57.900 --> 21:59.481
But I need you to call me back.

21:59.652 --> 22:03.065
You're the only one I can trust.
I've done something horrible.

22:12.248 --> 22:13.579
[BAG SQUISHING]

22:36.022 --> 22:38.764
-Huh!
-Didn't mean to scare you, pal.

22:38.941 --> 22:42.058
I saw your ambulance
while I was doing my rounds.

22:42.486 --> 22:43.692
Is everything okay back here?

22:43.863 --> 22:49.529
Oh, yeah, yeah. It's just a false alarm.
Probably a prank. It happens all the time.

22:55.082 --> 22:58.666
Hey, that's blood.

23:01.714 --> 23:04.046
-I really need to go.
-Hold on.

23:14.643 --> 23:16.770
GUARD:
Sweet Mary and Joseph.

23:16.937 --> 23:19.019
What the hell did you put in there?

23:20.357 --> 23:21.858
What did you do?

23:22.026 --> 23:25.985
It's not my fault. I blacked out.
I couldn't control it.

23:28.282 --> 23:32.150
Okay, listen to me,
you need to go right now.

23:32.328 --> 23:35.991
I'm not going anywhere.
You aren't either until the cops get here.

23:36.165 --> 23:37.826
[DAVIS GRUNTING]

23:42.838 --> 23:44.669
Run.

23:51.138 --> 23:52.298
[GUNSHOTS]

23:52.473 --> 23:53.633
[GUARD SCREAMS]

23:53.808 --> 23:55.173
[FLESH RIPPING]

23:55.351 --> 23:57.342
[GUESTS APPLAUDING]

24:00.397 --> 24:02.388
[LIGHT PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

24:03.150 --> 24:06.517
EMCEE: Now we'd like to ask Chloe's escort
to join her on the dance ﬂoor.

24:06.695 --> 24:08.435
Hey, Clark.

24:09.490 --> 24:10.650
It's time to boogie.

24:17.623 --> 24:19.454
I know, it's weird, isn't it?

24:19.625 --> 24:20.865
A little.

24:22.670 --> 24:24.786
Thank you for letting us
have our wedding here.

24:24.964 --> 24:26.420
CLARK:
Yeah, well...

24:27.216 --> 24:28.501
...it's the least I can do.

24:28.676 --> 24:30.007
[CHLOE CHUCKLES]

24:31.053 --> 24:33.635
You were always the best friend
I ever could have had.

24:35.641 --> 24:38.303
You say that like something's changed.

24:38.477 --> 24:39.808
Clark, trust me.

24:39.979 --> 24:44.143
We've been through too much together,
nothing is gonna make me forget that.

24:46.235 --> 24:47.725
You're right.

24:49.864 --> 24:53.482
The important thing is that your life
is everything you want it to be.

24:56.203 --> 24:57.864
It is.

24:58.330 --> 25:01.914
It's like I've been carrying around
this weight...

25:02.084 --> 25:05.576
...and I don't know why,
but a few days ago...

25:06.255 --> 25:08.496
...I ﬁnally let go.

25:09.091 --> 25:11.207
Like I can move on.

25:14.972 --> 25:16.803
Okay, C.K...

25:16.974 --> 25:19.181
...my turn to dance with my wife.

25:26.734 --> 25:29.601
[GUESTS APPLAUDING]

25:31.614 --> 25:33.605
[SAXOPHONE PLAYING
ROMANTIC MUSIC]

25:36.118 --> 25:39.281
Guess I can give
these well-heeled puppies a rest.

26:46.689 --> 26:48.304
CHLOE:
No way!

26:48.482 --> 26:50.689
I can't believe it.

26:51.527 --> 26:52.687
Oh, my God.

26:53.779 --> 26:55.770
[LAUGHS]

26:56.824 --> 26:58.360
CHLOE:
Hey.

27:24.685 --> 27:26.767
Great, thank you.

27:31.900 --> 27:33.811
You want a glass with that?

27:35.654 --> 27:38.691
Oliver. Just the person
I wanna see right now.

27:38.866 --> 27:40.197
[CH UCKLES]

27:40.367 --> 27:43.404
So, uh, you wanna tell me
what started this Lost Weekend?

27:44.413 --> 27:46.199
Go and enjoy the party.

27:46.373 --> 27:50.332
Trust me, it'll be a real buzz kill
to listen to me whine like Patsy Cline.

27:51.086 --> 27:52.747
Yeah, you're probably right.

27:52.921 --> 27:56.630
You know, um, I may not be at the top
of your conﬁdant list...

27:56.800 --> 27:59.633
...but if you ever wanna talk, I'm here.

28:07.603 --> 28:11.437
I'm just having all these feelings
and I don't know what they mean.

28:12.775 --> 28:14.106
Oh.

28:15.277 --> 28:17.393
Well, who's the lucky guy?

28:19.782 --> 28:21.113
[SIGHS]

28:21.575 --> 28:25.363
Having this conversation
with an ex is bad enough...

28:25.537 --> 28:28.950
...without turning up the awkward dial.

28:29.124 --> 28:30.455
[CH UCKLES]

28:31.960 --> 28:34.622
Well, you know,
there's moving on in theory...

28:34.797 --> 28:38.130
...and then there's the moment
that it actually happens.

28:39.676 --> 28:41.177
If you like, we can start now...

28:41.345 --> 28:44.007
...and I'll just be a really good friend.

28:46.558 --> 28:47.889
Okay.

28:48.060 --> 28:49.516
Okay.

28:54.024 --> 28:58.893
It's like I was going along
and itjust snuck up on me.

29:00.697 --> 29:04.565
And I tried to ignore it,
but then there are these moments...

29:04.743 --> 29:06.483
...that you can't.

29:08.914 --> 29:11.246
Maybe I was reading it wrong.

29:13.001 --> 29:14.332
And to add insult to injury...

29:14.503 --> 29:17.791
...it all went down
at tonight's tribute to romantic bliss.

29:22.553 --> 29:23.884
[SIGHS]

29:27.141 --> 29:29.928
I know it sounds sappy...

29:32.229 --> 29:34.345
...but I thought...

29:35.524 --> 29:37.515
...just for a minute...

29:37.818 --> 29:39.024
[SIGHS]

29:39.194 --> 29:41.185
...someone needed me.

29:44.741 --> 29:47.357
Well, I'm sure he needs you, Lois.

29:47.953 --> 29:49.284
[SCOFFS]

29:49.746 --> 29:53.580
That's sweet of you to say,
but how do you know?

29:55.419 --> 29:56.909
Because I know Clark.

30:04.511 --> 30:06.376
[GUESTS APPLAUDING]

30:08.849 --> 30:10.180
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

30:29.161 --> 30:31.243
Chloe's glad you came.

30:36.960 --> 30:39.337
I could have used some warning.

30:47.095 --> 30:49.381
You weren't planning on coming back,
were you?

30:49.556 --> 30:52.263
Yeah, not until a few hours ago.

31:00.567 --> 31:02.603
So, what changed your mind?

31:08.909 --> 31:11.571
I'm not expecting you to say it was me.

31:15.999 --> 31:20.618
I read about the mysterious blur
saving lives in Metropolis.

31:21.421 --> 31:24.629
I'm proud of you, Clark.
It's who you should have been all along.

31:25.968 --> 31:27.879
Does that mean you're happy you left?

31:31.181 --> 31:34.799
It was the hardest decision
I have ever had to make.

31:36.478 --> 31:39.936
But I'm glad
that I ﬁnally had the guts to do it.

31:50.033 --> 31:52.775
I would have died
before I admitted this...

31:52.953 --> 31:55.365
...but I used to sit on my front porch...

31:55.539 --> 32:00.283
...and look across the ﬁeld at this barn,
imagining a summer wedding here.

32:01.503 --> 32:05.212
Of course, I always thought
I'd play a bigger part in it.

32:06.300 --> 32:09.508
You probably would have
if I had given you Chloe's wedding gift.

32:13.765 --> 32:18.008
I had Jor-EI erase all the memories
that Chloe had of the real me.

32:21.565 --> 32:24.272
I wonder if that would've made things
different between us.

32:25.819 --> 32:30.188
I understood the lies that you told me
that protect your identity.

32:31.199 --> 32:34.612
But I could never forgive you
for taking that away from me.

32:34.786 --> 32:36.777
You can't mean that.

32:37.914 --> 32:39.700
Lana, it turned your life upside down.

32:39.875 --> 32:42.787
Maybe it was exactly what it needed.

32:44.588 --> 32:46.874
I could have landed
a lot of places in my life, Clark.

32:47.049 --> 32:50.462
But without you,
none of them would have led me here.

32:55.766 --> 32:57.506
So that's it?

33:00.103 --> 33:01.934
It's all over?

33:05.651 --> 33:07.437
It's that easy?

33:08.070 --> 33:09.935
No.

33:11.740 --> 33:13.901
But where I am now...

33:14.076 --> 33:17.193
...for the ﬁrst time, it feels right.

33:21.249 --> 33:24.286
Clark, I know neither of us could say it...

33:25.921 --> 33:30.210
...but maybe Clark Kent and Lana Lang
just weren't meant to end up together.

33:30.384 --> 33:31.419
WOMAN:
Kiss.

33:31.593 --> 33:35.177
GUESTS [CHANTING]:
Kiss, kiss, kiss.

33:35.347 --> 33:37.008
[GUESTS CHEERING]

33:51.947 --> 33:54.029
WOMAN:
Cut the cake.

34:11.299 --> 34:12.914
[THUD FROM ABOVE]

34:14.177 --> 34:15.212
Who was that?

34:15.387 --> 34:16.752
[GROWLING NEARBY]

34:17.264 --> 34:18.629
[THUD NEARBY]

34:21.476 --> 34:23.091
[GROWLING NEARBY]

34:24.312 --> 34:25.643
[THUD NEARBY]

34:26.022 --> 34:27.182
MAN:
Let's go.

34:27.357 --> 34:28.893
What is it?

34:29.860 --> 34:31.270
JIMMY:
I can't see.

34:33.739 --> 34:34.979
[GUESTS SCREAMING]

34:35.157 --> 34:37.364
MAN 1:
Oh, my God. Somebody, help!

34:39.745 --> 34:41.076
MAN 2:
We gotta go. You okay?

34:41.246 --> 34:42.782
CLARK:
Lana!

34:46.626 --> 34:48.162
MAN 3:
What is that thing?

34:49.838 --> 34:51.248
I'm okay. Go.

34:51.840 --> 34:53.501
MAN 4:
I can't see a thing.

34:56.011 --> 34:57.797
COLIN:
Oh, my God!

34:59.473 --> 35:02.010
MAN 5: Get out-- Get out of--
Get out of my way.

35:02.184 --> 35:03.845
MAN 6:
Get them out of here!

35:08.190 --> 35:09.805
Somebody help!

35:09.983 --> 35:11.314
Somebody help!

35:21.036 --> 35:22.367
[GRUNTS]

35:25.457 --> 35:27.118
[G ROANING]

35:35.133 --> 35:37.044
COLIN:
This isn't happening.

35:37.219 --> 35:39.255
This can't be happening.

35:40.722 --> 35:42.428
[COLIN SCREAMS]

35:42.599 --> 35:44.260
[FLESH RIPPING]

35:50.315 --> 35:51.816
Jimmy, don't!

35:55.487 --> 35:56.943
lib}

36:01.243 --> 36:02.779
Jimmy.

36:03.036 --> 36:05.152
Jimmy, please hold on.

36:08.416 --> 36:10.407
Hold on, Jimmy.

36:10.710 --> 36:12.917
Please don't leave me.

36:35.193 --> 36:37.605
DOOMSDAY:
Chloe.

36:52.460 --> 36:54.121
It's too late.

36:54.880 --> 36:56.541
That thing took Chloe.

37:25.994 --> 37:27.700
Any word on Chloe?

37:28.872 --> 37:30.112
No.

37:30.290 --> 37:33.373
But I'm meeting with Oliver.
He's using every satellite in his company...

37:33.543 --> 37:36.455
...to try to track down
where that thing might've taken her.

37:38.173 --> 37:39.663
Are you all right?

37:44.971 --> 37:47.178
Clark, there's nothing more
you can do for me.

37:47.349 --> 37:49.089
You don't need to stay.

37:52.020 --> 37:53.260
I know.

37:56.983 --> 37:58.359
I need to ﬁnd Chloe.

38:04.532 --> 38:06.113
[AMBULANCE SIREN WAILING]

38:09.537 --> 38:11.118
Lois.

38:12.916 --> 38:14.622
How are you holding up?

38:15.251 --> 38:17.333
Jimmy's in bad shape.

38:18.004 --> 38:20.541
The nurse said they had him stabilized.

38:20.715 --> 38:24.173
But he's not out of the woods.
He has severe internal bleeding.

38:24.344 --> 38:28.428
They're medevacing him to Star City
to one of the country's top surgeons.

38:29.516 --> 38:31.006
I'm gonna go with him.

38:33.228 --> 38:35.719
I'll stay there until I hear from...

38:36.231 --> 38:37.391
...Chloe.

38:40.527 --> 38:42.643
Why did this have to happen to her?

38:44.406 --> 38:47.398
Why do these terrible things
keep happening all around us?

38:51.204 --> 38:52.865
I promise...

38:54.165 --> 38:55.746
...we're gonna get Chloe back.

39:01.047 --> 39:02.912
What if we can't?

40:54.369 --> 40:57.361
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

42:02.020 --> 42:04.011
[ENGLISH SDH]
